      "Description": "This lesson explores how deepfake technology is reshaping the media and entertainment industries, from synthetic actors and digitally recreated voices to manipulated footage that can be difficult to distinguish from genuine content. You will learn about the key risks these technologies pose, including issues around consent, copyright, and the potential for reputational harm to performers and public figures. We will look at real-world examples of how deepfakes have already been used within film, music, and online media, both creatively and harmfully. By the end of this lesson, you will have a clearer understanding of how to recognise manipulated content and why it matters for audiences, creators, and industry professionals alike.",
